Defendant Steve Anthony Hardin in court with attorney Reyna Ivonne Morales.  Defendant Steve Anthony Hardin in custody.  Christopher A. Liegel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case scheduled for Plea/Sentencing.     
Defendant sworn in. 
AS TO COUNT 1 and 2  - 
The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Jury Instructions and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.
Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting.
AS TO COUNT 3 -
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered COUNT 3 dismissed.

Case proceeds to sentencing. Statements made as to sentencing. 

AS TO COUNT 1- 
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 30 DAYS in the House of Correction CONCURRENT with COUNT 2 and revocation, with credit for 79 DAYS time served and Huber privileges for work and child care. TIME SERVED DISPOSITION. 
The Court ordered the defendant to pay all applicable costs, surcharges including DV surcharge and assessments while on probation in COUNT 2; any balance remaining unpaid at that time is to be converted to a civil judgment against the defendant.
The Court ordered the defendant to provide a DNA sample; pay surcharge.
AS TO COUNT 2-  
Court ordered defendant to serve 1 YEAR in the House of Correction consecutive to any sentence; straight time; no good time credit.
Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS with the following conditions:
- Court ordered 90 days of condition time in the House of Correction, with Huber privileges for work and child care.
- Successfully complete an anger management/a Batterers Intervention program;
- Mental health evaluation and take all prescribed medication; Attend parenting class; 
- AODA assessment and comply with any treatment;
- Maintain absolute sobriety;
- Attend treatment and counseling programs as determined by agent; 
- No contact with the victim without the approval of the court or Department of Corrections; 
- 3rd party contact for the purpose of time with children as approved by agent;
- Obtain/maintain employment;
- Obtain GED or HSED;
- Court costs, surcharges including DV surcharge to be paid; failure to pay will result in a Civil Judgment. 
- Restitution set at ZERO;
- Pay all supervision fees;
- Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge. 

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting 
Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Memorandum of Conditions of Probation;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
signed Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgement;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
